P(Y_{1} = c_{2} \mid X_{1}=\Sexpr{data[1]},\Theta= \theta^{(0)}) &= \frac{P(X_{1}=\Sexpr{data[1]},Y_{1} = c_{2} \mid \Theta= \theta^{(0)})}{P(X_1 = \Sexpr{data[1]} \mid \Theta= \theta^{(0)})} = \Sexpr{posteriors[idx,2]} \nonumber \\
